The paper deals with visual analysis in resource-limited scenarios, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed approach involves sensor fusion techniques and multi-view representation learning, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves sparse coding and joint sparsity, which are techniques used in signal processing and machine learning, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also involves optimization techniques, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of norm-based regularization, which is a technique used in information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
